ticTacToe

Class Outcome

  • java.lang.Object
    • ticTacToe.Outcome

  • public class Outcome
extends java.lang.Object
    This is a game outcome: a data structure containing a game (state), a move, a reward, and the next target game state. From your lectures, this is essentially a (s,a,r,s') tuple, where s is the source state, a is the action taken, r is the reward received locally, and s' is the state we transitioned into.
